  "name": "Forgemasters",
  "type": "feat",
  "_id": "SWVg6Yws4NkqfkEJ",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Kajiya.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong data-start=\"56\" data-end=\"79\">Kajiya Clan members</strong> are taught the secrets of metallurgy early on in their lives. Beginning at 1st level, you gain 1 rank of Mastery in either Armorsmith Kits or Weaponsmith Kits. Beginning at 7th level, you gain a 2nd rank of Mastery, and at 15th level, you gain a 3rd.</p><p data-start=\"334\" data-end=\"1007\">Also at 1st level, when in possession of either an Armorsmith Kit or Weaponsmith Kit, as a Bonus Action, you may choose to spend a charge to produce a Forge Hammer and equip it. Forge Hammers are small blacksmith hammers in appearance, deal <strong data-start=\"575\" data-end=\"602\">1d6 + your Strength Mod</strong> in Bludgeoning damage, have the <strong data-start=\"635\" data-end=\"644\">Light</strong> and <strong data-start=\"649\" data-end=\"667\">Thrown (30/60)</strong> properties, and belong to the <strong data-start=\"698\" data-end=\"707\">Power</strong> weapon group. While equipped, you cannot be disarmed of your Forge Hammer, and it cannot be destroyed by way of jutsu. Stronger kits produce stronger Forge Hammers, with each stage of kit greater adding a +1 to the Forge Hammer (<strong data-start=\"937\" data-end=\"1003\">Greater Charge = +1, Superior Charge = +2, Supreme Charge = +3</strong>).</p><p data-start=\"1009\" data-end=\"1105\">Beginning at 11th level, your Forge Hammer's base damage becomes <strong data-start=\"1074\" data-end=\"1102\">1d10 + your Strength Mod</strong>.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
